                    <span>Sonny Barger is one of my heroes, not because of what he believes, but rather because he believes. This book portrays a deeply principled man. We may not hold the same principles, but his aren't that different from ours. The important thing is that the man reflected in these pages holds principles, which is more than many people leading less colorful lives can say.</span>
                  
